=begin

 this partial inserts the default footer line for all types of pages;
 the feature_id is picked up from the controller's setting, UNLESS
 you choose to replace this value by a local variable passed to this
 partial (e.g. in help pages).

 A specific help page may be requested via the help_page parameter.
 The default is to use the help text for the controller.

 Pass the feature_id as parameter, and optionally details information
 for the change request:
 
 Example (from User view)

 < %= render partial: 'shared/footer',
   locals: { feature_identifier: FEATURE_ID_XYZ, cr_details: 'here', help_page: 'stats' } % >

=end
-%>

